      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/29/2",
      "text": [
        " : \"اَلْفِضَّةُ بِالْفِضَّةِ مِثْلٌ بِمِثْلٍ وَ اَلذَّهَبُ بِالذَّهَبِ مِثْلٌ بِمِثْلٍ لَيْسَ فِيهِ زِيَادَةٌ وَ لاَ نَظِرَةٌ اَلزَّائِدُ وَ اَلْمُسْتَزِيدُ فِي اَلنَّارِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4037 - Hammad narrated from al-Halabi, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"Silver for silver must be equal, and gold for gold must be equal, there should be neither an increase nor a delay. The one who gives extra and the one who demands extra will be in the Fire.\""
        ]
      }
    },
